WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.890 align:middle line:10%
>> A powerful FDA-approved
anesthetic drug once used

00:00:04.890 --> 00:00:08.910 align:middle line:10%
mainly in operating rooms and
on the battlefield is quickly

00:00:08.910 --> 00:00:11.850 align:middle line:10%
gaining ground as one of
the most promising therapies

00:00:11.850 --> 00:00:15.940 align:middle line:10%
for treatment resistant
mental health conditions.

00:00:15.940 --> 00:00:17.470 align:middle line:90%
This is "Gaia News."

00:00:17.470 --> 00:00:24.630 align:middle line:90%


00:00:24.630 --> 00:00:28.440 align:middle line:10%
First discovered as an
anesthetic in the 1950s,

00:00:28.440 --> 00:00:30.720 align:middle line:10%
ketamine has since been
used in the treatment

00:00:30.720 --> 00:00:33.150 align:middle line:10%
of a wide range of
physical conditions,

00:00:33.150 --> 00:00:36.150 align:middle line:10%
especially in pain management.

00:00:36.150 --> 00:00:39.210 align:middle line:84%
Starting in the
early 1970s, doctors

00:00:39.210 --> 00:00:41.010 align:middle line:84%
began to find that
it can also be

00:00:41.010 --> 00:00:43.650 align:middle line:84%
very effective in
alleviating mental health

00:00:43.650 --> 00:00:49.740 align:middle line:84%
issues, such as depression,
anxiety, PTSD, and addiction.

00:00:49.740 --> 00:00:51.960 align:middle line:84%
Today, it is ever
more frequently

00:00:51.960 --> 00:00:56.310 align:middle line:84%
being studied and legally used
as an off-label medication

00:00:56.310 --> 00:00:58.560 align:middle line:84%
to manage conditions
that are particularly

00:00:58.560 --> 00:01:02.550 align:middle line:84%
resistant to treatment with
conventional pharmaceuticals.

00:01:02.550 --> 00:01:05.160 align:middle line:84%
The latest in a series
of recent studies

00:01:05.160 --> 00:01:07.920 align:middle line:84%
has found that ketamine can
quickly and dramatically

00:01:07.920 --> 00:01:11.370 align:middle line:84%
decrease chronic
suicidal thoughts.

00:01:11.370 --> 00:01:14.070 align:middle line:10%
Dr. Naveen Thomas
is a psychiatrist

00:01:14.070 --> 00:01:17.760 align:middle line:10%
who has been using ketamine
in his practice for years.

00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:20.710 align:middle line:10%
>> I and many of my colleagues
have had, of course,

00:01:20.710 --> 00:01:25.290 align:middle line:10%
tremendous success in using
ketamine in people who are

00:01:25.290 --> 00:01:27.330 align:middle line:10%
really suffering
from depression.

00:01:27.330 --> 00:01:31.530 align:middle line:84%
I've had a lot of success
in treating people

00:01:31.530 --> 00:01:34.320 align:middle line:84%
with post-traumatic
stress disorder.

00:01:34.320 --> 00:01:37.080 align:middle line:84%
And some of these folks
have spent years and years

00:01:37.080 --> 00:01:38.580 align:middle line:84%
doing absolutely
the best they could

00:01:38.580 --> 00:01:42.460 align:middle line:84%
using such a wide variety of
the conventional treatments,

00:01:42.460 --> 00:01:44.910 align:middle line:84%
be they various medication
treatments, be they

00:01:44.910 --> 00:01:46.620 align:middle line:90%
various forms of psychotherapy.

00:01:46.620 --> 00:01:52.170 align:middle line:84%
We've seen really
wonderful effects.

00:01:52.170 --> 00:01:55.470 align:middle line:84%
>> While the mechanism by which
ketamine works isn't entirely

00:01:55.470 --> 00:01:58.530 align:middle line:84%
clear, it is known that
it increases the amount

00:01:58.530 --> 00:02:02.280 align:middle line:84%
of a neurotransmitter
called glutamine.

00:02:02.280 --> 00:02:06.420 align:middle line:84%
This novel process likely
affects mood, thought patterns

00:02:06.420 --> 00:02:09.720 align:middle line:84%
and cognition by producing
a non-ordinary state

00:02:09.720 --> 00:02:11.580 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness.

00:02:11.580 --> 00:02:14.730 align:middle line:84%
It is also thought that as
with other psychedelics,

00:02:14.730 --> 00:02:17.190 align:middle line:84%
ketamine quiets the
brain's default mode

00:02:17.190 --> 00:02:20.580 align:middle line:84%
network, a dynamic
set of brain systems

00:02:20.580 --> 00:02:24.600 align:middle line:84%
that are active when we are
not engaged in a specific task.

00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:26.910 align:middle line:10%
Researchers believe it
is where we construct

00:02:26.910 --> 00:02:29.910 align:middle line:10%
the narrative of who
we are, and where

00:02:29.910 --> 00:02:33.000 align:middle line:10%
we can get stuck in
destructive thought patterns.

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:35.850 align:middle line:84%
Ketamine is thought to exert
its effect by opening up

00:02:35.850 --> 00:02:38.580 align:middle line:90%
new pathways for thought.

00:02:38.580 --> 00:02:42.460 align:middle line:10%
>> In many mental
health conditions,

00:02:42.460 --> 00:02:45.660 align:middle line:10%
one of the challenges
that people struggle with,

00:02:45.660 --> 00:02:51.090 align:middle line:10%
is that self narrative can
often become rigid and fixed

00:02:51.090 --> 00:02:54.120 align:middle line:10%
and often, quite
negative in nature.

00:02:54.120 --> 00:02:58.110 align:middle line:84%
Ketamine at the right
doses, can even temporarily

00:02:58.110 --> 00:03:03.300 align:middle line:84%
